external_knowledge:
- 'Eastern Standard Time zone' is referred to as 'EST';
- In metaphorical terms, 'captains' represent 'users' who have created events;
- 'Anchors' symbolize 'events' created in the EST timezone;
- 'Casting more than two anchors' means creating more than two events in the EST timezone.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT users.first_name, users.last_name, users.role
FROM events
INNER JOIN users ON events.created_by = users.user_id;

external_knowledge:
- Active participants refer to those who have organized either meetings or tasks;
- Busier is defined here by having more unique event dates in the previous month (excluding the last week) compared to the events in the current month;
- Events are categorized as meetings or tasks, implying focus only on these categories.

sql:
SELECT *
FROM timezones
WHERE timezone_name = (SELECT timezone FROM events WHERE event_id = 1);

SELECT events.event_name, timezones.timezone_name
FROM events
JOIN timezones ON events.timezone = timezones.timezone_name;
